                {
                  "type": 1,
                  "content": {
                    "json": "## {acrCve} — {acrSW}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Overview\r\n| CVE ID | Severity | CVSS 3.0 | Fix status | Published |\r\n|---|---|---|---|---|\r\n| {acrCve} | {acrCSev} | {acrCvss} | {acrFS} | {acrPub} |\r\n\r\n**CVSS vector:** {acrVec}\r\n\r\n**Vendor:** {acrVend}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\n{acrCvDesc}\r\n\r\n{acrExtDesc}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Impact\r\n{acrImpact}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Exploitability\r\n| Exploit steps published | In exploit kit | Exploit steps verified |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| {acrEP} | {acrEK} | {acrEV} |\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Remediation\r\n{acrRemed}\r\n\r\n**Fix version:** {acrFixVer}\r\n\r\nIf no vendor-specific guidance is shown above, update **{acrSW}** to the latest fixed version. Review CI/CD pipelines and container images for instances of the vulnerable software.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### References\r\n{acrRefs}\r\n",
                    "style": "info"
                  },
                  "conditionalVisibility": {
                    "parameterName": "acrCVSel",
                    "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                    "value": "true"
                  },
                  "name": "acr_card"
                }
              ]
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
