                  "type": 1,
                  "content": {
                    "json": "## {ecrCve} — {ecrSW}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Overview\r\n| CVE ID | Severity | CVSS 3.0 | Fix status | Published |\r\n|---|---|---|---|---|\r\n| {ecrCve} | {ecrCSev} | {ecrCvss} | {ecrFS} | {ecrPub} |\r\n\r\n**CVSS vector:** {ecrVec}\r\n\r\n**Vendor:** {ecrVend}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\n{ecrCvDesc}\r\n\r\n{ecrExtDesc}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Impact\r\n{ecrImpact}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Exploitability\r\n| Exploit steps published | In exploit kit | Exploit steps verified |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| {ecrEP} | {ecrEK} | {ecrEV} |\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Remediation\r\n{ecrRemed}\r\n\r\n**Fix version:** {ecrFixVer}\r\n\r\nIf no vendor-specific guidance is shown above, update **{ecrSW}** to the latest fixed version. Review CI/CD pipelines and container images for instances of the vulnerable software.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### References\r\n{ecrRefs}\r\n",
                    "style": "info"
                  },
                  "conditionalVisibility": {
                    "parameterName": "ecrCVSel",
                    "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                    "value": "true"
                  },
                  "name": "ecr_card"
                }
              ]
            },
