                  "type": 1,
                  "content": {
                    "json": "## {gcpCve} — {gcpSW}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Overview\r\n| CVE ID | Severity | CVSS 3.0 | Fix status | Published |\r\n|---|---|---|---|---|\r\n| {gcpCve} | {gcpCSev} | {gcpCvss} | {gcpFS} | {gcpPub} |\r\n\r\n**CVSS vector:** {gcpVec}\r\n\r\n**Vendor:** {gcpVend}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\n{gcpCvDesc}\r\n\r\n{gcpExtDesc}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Impact\r\n{gcpImpact}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Exploitability\r\n| Exploit steps published | In exploit kit | Exploit steps verified |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| {gcpEP} | {gcpEK} | {gcpEV} |\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Remediation\r\n{gcpRemed}\r\n\r\n**Fix version:** {gcpFixVer}\r\n\r\nIf no vendor-specific guidance is shown above, update **{gcpSW}** to the latest fixed version. Review CI/CD pipelines and container images for instances of the vulnerable software.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### References\r\n{gcpRefs}\r\n",
                    "style": "info"
                  },
                  "conditionalVisibility": {
                    "parameterName": "gcpCVSel",
                    "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                    "value": "true"
                  },
                  "name": "gcp_card"
                }
              ]
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "regcloud",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "gcp"
            },
            "name": "reg_gcp"
          }
        ]
      },
      "conditionalVisibility": {
        "parameterName": "tab",
        "comparison": "isEqualTo",
        "value": "registry"
      },
      "name": "registry_parent"
    },
