                    "json": "## {aksCve} — {aksSW}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Overview\r\n| CVE ID | Severity | CVSS 3.0 | Fix status | Published |\r\n|---|---|---|---|---|\r\n| {aksCve} | {aksCSev} | {aksCvss} | {aksFS} | {aksPub} |\r\n\r\n**CVSS vector:** {aksVec}\r\n\r\n**Vendor:** {aksVend}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\n{aksCvDesc}\r\n\r\n{aksExtDesc}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Impact\r\n{aksImpact}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Exploitability\r\n| Exploit steps published | In exploit kit | Exploit steps verified |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| {aksEP} | {aksEK} | {aksEV} |\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Remediation\r\n{aksRemed}\r\n\r\n**Fix version:** {aksFixVer}\r\n\r\nIf no vendor-specific guidance is shown above, update **{aksSW}** to the latest fixed version. Review running containers and deployments for instances of the vulnerable software.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### References\r\n{aksRefs}\r\n",
                    "style": "info"
