                {
                  "type": 1,
                  "content": {
                    "json": "## {gkeCve} — {gkeSW}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Overview\r\n| CVE ID | Severity | CVSS 3.0 | Fix status | Published |\r\n|---|---|---|---|---|\r\n| {gkeCve} | {gkeCSev} | {gkeCvss} | {gkeFS} | {gkePub} |\r\n\r\n**CVSS vector:** {gkeVec}\r\n\r\n**Vendor:** {gkeVend}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\n{gkeCvDesc}\r\n\r\n{gkeExtDesc}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Impact\r\n{gkeImpact}\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Exploitability\r\n| Exploit steps published | In exploit kit | Exploit steps verified |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| {gkeEP} | {gkeEK} | {gkeEV} |\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Remediation\r\n{gkeRemed}\r\n\r\n**Fix version:** {gkeFixVer}\r\n\r\nIf no vendor-specific guidance is shown above, update **{gkeSW}** to the latest fixed version. Review running containers and deployments for instances of the vulnerable software.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### References\r\n{gkeRefs}\r\n",
                    "style": "info"
                  },
                  "conditionalVisibility": {
                    "parameterName": "gkeCVSel",
                    "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                    "value": "true"
                  },
                  "name": "gke_card"
                }
              ]
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
